WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:14.140
The Truth Machine by Norman Whitney, a Heinemann guided reader at beginner level.

00:14.140 --> 00:28.120
Copyright Heinemann International, first recorded 1982, this edition 1992.

00:28.120 --> 00:31.640
Chapter 1 Success for Professor Verity

00:31.640 --> 00:36.880
Success, cried Professor Verity.

00:36.880 --> 00:39.040
My new invention is ready.

00:39.040 --> 00:41.000
It is now complete.

00:41.000 --> 00:44.760
I shall call it the Truth Machine.

00:44.760 --> 00:48.920
The professor ran to the telephone and phoned the newspaper office.

00:48.920 --> 00:51.560
He told them about the Truth Machine.

00:52.560 --> 00:55.800
Come to my laboratory, he said.

00:55.800 --> 00:58.520
You will see my new invention.

00:58.520 --> 01:01.960
I call it the Truth Machine.

01:01.960 --> 01:07.360
Please give us your name and address, said the girl at the newspaper office.

01:07.360 --> 01:10.320
We'll send a reporter immediately.

01:10.320 --> 01:15.840
The professor gave the girl his name and address.

01:15.840 --> 01:19.680
Will the reporter be here soon, he asked?

01:19.680 --> 01:23.400
Yes, of course, replied the girl.

01:23.400 --> 01:26.640
Good, said Professor Verity.

01:26.640 --> 01:29.800
He smiled, he waited.

01:29.800 --> 01:33.760
The reporter soon arrived at the laboratory.

01:33.760 --> 01:36.640
Who can use the Truth Machine, Professor?

01:36.640 --> 01:38.080
He asked.

01:38.080 --> 01:42.280
Anybody can use it, replied Professor Verity.

01:42.280 --> 01:44.920
But how does the machine work?

01:44.920 --> 01:46.800
Asked the reporter.

01:46.800 --> 01:48.680
The professor laughed.

01:48.680 --> 01:51.760
That's the secret, he said.

01:51.760 --> 01:53.960
But I can tell you this.

01:53.960 --> 01:58.960
The questioner sits in the little chair, eyes sit at the controls,

01:58.960 --> 02:02.160
and the Truth speaker sits in the big chair.

02:02.160 --> 02:05.760
The Truth speaker always speaks the truth.

02:05.760 --> 02:08.400
He cannot tell lies.

02:08.400 --> 02:10.760
The professor smiled.

02:10.760 --> 02:13.360
Why did you make the Truth Machine?

02:13.360 --> 02:15.520
Asked the reporter.

02:15.520 --> 02:20.880
I love Truth, said Professor Verity, and I hate lies.

02:20.880 --> 02:24.720
I love good people, and I hate bad people.

02:24.720 --> 02:28.000
I love peace, and I hate war.

02:28.000 --> 02:31.760
The Truth Machine loves Truth, good people, and peace.

02:31.760 --> 02:36.680
It hates lies, bad people, and war.

02:36.680 --> 02:40.520
The reporter wrote all this in his notebook.

02:40.520 --> 02:45.320
Soon everybody will know about the Truth Machine, said the professor.

02:45.320 --> 02:48.240
It will be a success.

02:48.240 --> 02:55.600
The reporter thanked the professor, and hurried back to his newspaper office.

02:55.600 --> 02:57.720
Professor Verity was right.

02:57.720 --> 03:02.520
Soon millions of people knew about the Truth Machine.

03:02.520 --> 03:04.680
The professor was on the radio.

03:04.680 --> 03:07.120
He was on the television, too.

03:07.120 --> 03:13.080
All over the world, newspapers and magazines wrote about Professor Verity and the Truth

03:13.080 --> 03:15.120
Machine.

03:15.120 --> 03:18.000
Many people wrote to Professor Verity.

03:18.000 --> 03:24.560
Rich people, poor people, young people, old people, everybody sent letters.

03:24.560 --> 03:28.280
The Truth Machine was a success.

03:28.280 --> 03:31.240
Thank you, wrote one woman.

03:31.240 --> 03:34.240
Wonderful, wrote another.

03:34.240 --> 03:36.680
Good luck, wrote one man.

03:36.680 --> 03:38.600
I am sending you some money.

03:38.600 --> 03:41.120
It will help your work.

03:41.120 --> 03:43.280
Many people sent money.

03:43.280 --> 03:51.960
Some sent coins, others sent banknotes, and others sent checks and money orders.

03:51.960 --> 03:55.680
Then the professor chose his first clients.

03:55.680 --> 03:57.680
He read his letters many times.

03:57.680 --> 04:01.040
First, he chose a hundred letters.

04:01.040 --> 04:03.480
Then he chose fifty of them.

04:03.480 --> 04:06.040
Then he chose ten names.

04:06.040 --> 04:09.920
Finally, he chose three people.

04:09.920 --> 04:17.280
This is Seeker from Australia, Inspector Sack from South America, and Dr. Simple from

04:17.280 --> 04:19.480
the United States.

04:19.480 --> 04:25.680
Professor Verity wrote to them, Please come and see me, he wrote.

04:25.680 --> 04:27.920
You will be one of my first clients.

04:39.920 --> 04:45.040
Chapter 2.

04:45.040 --> 04:49.520
Three visitors for Professor Verity.

04:49.520 --> 04:53.360
Two weeks later, Professor Verity had a visitor.

04:53.360 --> 04:55.280
It was Mrs. Seeker.

04:55.280 --> 04:57.200
She was from Australia.

04:57.200 --> 04:59.280
She was a housewife.

04:59.280 --> 05:00.760
She was afraid.

05:00.760 --> 05:04.080
Can I help you, Mrs. Seeker?

05:04.080 --> 05:05.640
Ask the professor.

05:05.640 --> 05:08.560
Yes, Mrs. Seeker replied.

05:08.720 --> 05:12.000
I wrote to you about the truth machine.

05:12.000 --> 05:14.480
I know, said the professor.

05:14.480 --> 05:16.600
You will be my first client.

05:16.600 --> 05:18.520
Don't be afraid.

05:18.520 --> 05:20.760
Oh, said Mrs. Seeker.

05:20.760 --> 05:23.640
I will not be your first client, Professor.

05:23.640 --> 05:26.920
Your first client will be my husband.

05:26.920 --> 05:30.160
Your husband, said Professor Verity.

05:30.160 --> 05:32.560
The professor was surprised.

05:32.560 --> 05:35.560
But your husband didn't write to me.

05:35.640 --> 05:39.000
No, he didn't, said Mrs. Seeker.

05:39.000 --> 05:41.360
I wrote to you.

05:41.360 --> 05:43.040
But what do you want?

05:43.040 --> 05:44.560
Ask the professor.

05:44.560 --> 05:47.000
Why are you here?

05:47.000 --> 05:49.960
Well, said Mrs. Seeker.

05:49.960 --> 05:53.480
My husband, Mrs. Seeker, stopped.

05:53.480 --> 05:54.840
She was crying.

05:54.840 --> 05:56.960
She was unhappy.

05:56.960 --> 06:00.880
My husband as Mrs. Seeker stopped again.

06:00.880 --> 06:03.600
She was crying again.

06:03.600 --> 06:07.160
Oh, said the professor quietly.

06:07.160 --> 06:11.600
Your husband has another woman.

06:11.600 --> 06:13.680
Yes, yes.

06:13.680 --> 06:15.400
Pride, Mrs. Seeker.

06:15.400 --> 06:17.200
But I don't know.

06:17.200 --> 06:19.000
Oh, I hate lies.

06:19.000 --> 06:21.000
I want the truth, Professor.

06:21.000 --> 06:25.280
I want the truth from my husband.

06:25.280 --> 06:27.000
But will he come here?

06:27.000 --> 06:28.920
Ask the professor.

06:28.920 --> 06:31.000
Oh, yes, he'll come.

06:31.000 --> 06:33.120
Said Mrs. Seeker.

06:33.120 --> 06:37.680
Well, bring him to my laboratory, said the professor.

06:37.680 --> 06:39.880
I'll help you, Mrs. Seeker.

06:39.880 --> 06:44.000
Of course, there will be a small charge, a fee.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.240
I'll pay anything, said Mrs. Seeker.

06:47.240 --> 06:48.760
I hate lies.

06:48.760 --> 06:51.760
I want the truth from my husband.

06:51.760 --> 06:55.560
Come here next Monday morning, said the professor.

06:55.560 --> 06:59.080
Everything will be ready.

06:59.080 --> 07:02.120
The next visitor was Inspector Sack.

07:02.120 --> 07:04.320
He was from South America.

07:04.320 --> 07:07.720
He was a policeman, and he had a gun.

07:07.720 --> 07:09.720
Hello, Professor!

07:09.720 --> 07:11.560
Said the inspector.

07:11.560 --> 07:15.200
The inspector had a loud voice.

07:15.200 --> 07:17.120
Where is it, Professor?

07:17.120 --> 07:18.280
He shouted.

07:18.280 --> 07:21.720
Where is the truth machine?

07:21.720 --> 07:26.400
It's here, Inspector, said Professor Verity quietly.

07:26.400 --> 07:29.440
You will be one of my first clients.

07:29.520 --> 07:33.720
All good, said the inspector.

07:33.720 --> 07:36.600
Inspector Sack walked up and down.

07:36.600 --> 07:38.080
Then he stopped.

07:38.080 --> 07:40.560
He looked at the professor.

07:40.560 --> 07:43.480
Crime, shouted Inspector Sack.

07:43.480 --> 07:47.480
Crime, crime, crime.

07:47.480 --> 07:51.240
Crime, asked the professor in a soft voice.

07:51.240 --> 07:55.280
Yes, crime, shouted Inspector Sack.

07:55.280 --> 07:57.400
I hate criminals.

07:57.400 --> 07:59.760
Murderers are criminals.

07:59.760 --> 08:01.600
They kill people.

08:01.600 --> 08:03.960
I hate murderers.

08:03.960 --> 08:06.080
Thieves are criminals.

08:06.080 --> 08:08.440
They take things from people.

08:08.440 --> 08:10.600
I hate thieves.

08:10.600 --> 08:13.400
And liars are criminals.

08:13.400 --> 08:15.400
They tell lies.

08:15.400 --> 08:18.320
I hate lies, Professor.

08:18.320 --> 08:21.960
I hate all criminals.

08:21.960 --> 08:25.080
But the truth machine will fight criminals,

08:25.080 --> 08:28.080
said Professor Verity quietly.

08:28.080 --> 08:30.960
There will be no more murderers and thieves.

08:30.960 --> 08:35.800
There will be no more lies and no more crime, Inspector.

08:35.800 --> 08:41.680
No more criminals and no more crime, shouted Inspector Sack.

08:41.680 --> 08:44.280
Excellent.

08:44.280 --> 08:48.520
Bring your criminals to me, Inspector, said the professor.

08:48.520 --> 08:52.600
Of course, there will be a small charge, a fee.

08:52.600 --> 08:53.720
Money?

08:53.720 --> 08:55.640
Shouted Inspector Sack.

08:55.640 --> 08:58.320
You shall have money, Professor.

08:58.320 --> 09:00.920
We are fighting crime, my friend.

09:00.920 --> 09:04.600
Of course, you shall have money.

09:04.600 --> 09:08.280
Thank you, Inspector, said Professor Verity.

09:08.280 --> 09:10.000
Thank you.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.560
Come here next Monday afternoon.

09:12.560 --> 09:14.880
Bring your criminals to me.

09:14.880 --> 09:15.960
Everything will be ready.

09:19.400 --> 09:21.680
Good morning, Professor Verity.

09:21.680 --> 09:24.520
My name is Dr. Simple.

09:24.520 --> 09:27.360
Dr. Simple was the third visitor.

09:27.360 --> 09:29.640
He was from the United States.

09:29.640 --> 09:31.640
He was a government official.

09:31.640 --> 09:34.720
He worked for the American government.

09:34.720 --> 09:38.240
Hello, Dr. Simple, said the professor.

09:38.240 --> 09:41.320
You will be one of my first clients.

09:41.320 --> 09:44.040
I know, said Dr. Simple.

09:44.040 --> 09:46.440
I will be your third client.

09:46.440 --> 09:50.920
The other two are Mrs. Seeker and Inspector Sack.

09:50.920 --> 09:53.520
Hello, said the professor.

09:53.520 --> 09:56.080
How do you know their names?

09:56.080 --> 09:58.920
Dr. Simple looked round.

09:58.920 --> 10:04.080
Spies, Professor Verity, said Dr. Simple quietly.

10:04.080 --> 10:06.200
Spies.

10:06.200 --> 10:09.520
Spies, asked Professor Verity.

10:09.520 --> 10:13.760
But Mrs. Seeker and Inspector Sack aren't spies.

10:13.760 --> 10:18.200
Of course, they are not spies, said Dr. Simple.

10:18.200 --> 10:19.880
He looked round.

10:19.880 --> 10:22.680
But I am.

10:22.680 --> 10:27.320
Oh, you are a spy, the professor asked.

10:27.320 --> 10:30.240
Yes, said Dr. Simple.

10:30.240 --> 10:32.600
I'm a spy.

10:32.600 --> 10:33.960
He looked round.

10:33.960 --> 10:37.120
He was looking for enemy spies.

10:37.120 --> 10:41.040
I fight for peace, said Dr. Simple.

10:41.040 --> 10:43.360
Professor Verity is smiled.

10:43.360 --> 10:47.560
Oh, I want peace too, the professor said.

10:47.560 --> 10:50.320
I know, said Dr. Simple.

10:50.320 --> 10:51.800
He smiled.

10:51.800 --> 10:53.920
You will help me, Professor.

10:53.920 --> 10:56.440
We have caught an enemy spy.

10:56.440 --> 10:58.560
He will not tell the truth.

10:58.560 --> 11:00.480
I will bring him here.

11:00.480 --> 11:02.120
I will be the questioner.

11:02.120 --> 11:05.000
He will be the truth speaker.

11:05.000 --> 11:07.120
Yes, said the professor.

11:07.120 --> 11:09.200
Please bring him here.

11:09.200 --> 11:13.960
Of course, Dr. Simple, there will be a small charge, a fee.

11:13.960 --> 11:15.920
Dr. Simple smiled.

11:15.920 --> 11:18.000
He looked round again.

11:18.000 --> 11:21.840
Of course, Professor, here is some money.

11:21.840 --> 11:25.840
Dr. Simple gave the professor a lot of money.

11:25.840 --> 11:29.160
Thank you, said the professor quietly.

11:29.160 --> 11:31.360
He looked round too.

11:31.360 --> 11:34.600
Come here with your spy next Monday evening.

11:34.600 --> 11:36.600
Everything will be ready.

11:36.600 --> 11:53.240
CHAPTER 3

11:53.240 --> 11:58.240
MONDAY A BUSY DAY FOR PROFESSOR Verity

11:58.240 --> 12:00.200
It was Monday morning.

12:00.200 --> 12:02.920
Mrs. Seeker came to the laboratory.

12:02.920 --> 12:04.920
Mr. Seeker came too.

12:05.360 --> 12:07.120
How are you, Professor?

12:07.120 --> 12:08.800
Said Mr. Seeker.

12:08.800 --> 12:12.840
Where is your truth, machine?

12:12.840 --> 12:14.840
Mr. Seeker laughed.

12:14.840 --> 12:17.920
Don't laugh, said his wife.

12:17.920 --> 12:19.520
She was afraid.

12:19.520 --> 12:21.960
Listen to the professor.

12:21.960 --> 12:24.680
Professor Verity spoke.

12:24.680 --> 12:27.880
Mrs. Seeker, you are the questioner.

12:27.880 --> 12:30.160
Sit in the small chair.

12:30.160 --> 12:33.400
Mr. Seeker, you are the truth speaker.

12:33.400 --> 12:36.360
Sit in the big chair.

12:36.360 --> 12:39.600
Mr. and Mrs. Seeker sat in their chairs.

12:39.600 --> 12:42.880
Mrs. Seeker looked at the professor.

12:42.880 --> 12:44.640
What shall I say?

12:44.640 --> 12:46.440
She asked.

12:46.440 --> 12:51.200
Ask your husband some easy questions, said the professor.

12:51.200 --> 12:54.000
She looked at her husband.

12:54.000 --> 12:55.800
What is your name?

12:55.800 --> 12:57.320
She asked.

12:57.320 --> 13:00.760
My name is Henry, said her husband.

13:00.760 --> 13:03.360
That was an easy question.

13:03.360 --> 13:05.320
He laughed.

13:05.320 --> 13:07.720
How old are you, Henry?

13:07.720 --> 13:09.640
Asked Mrs. Seeker.

13:09.640 --> 13:16.480
I'm 47, said Mr. Seeker.

13:16.480 --> 13:19.200
Mrs. Seeker looked at Professor Verity.

13:19.200 --> 13:20.800
She smiled.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.240
That's the truth, she said.

13:23.240 --> 13:26.800
He usually says 43.

13:26.840 --> 13:28.400
My husband is telling the truth.

13:31.400 --> 13:34.800
Good, said Professor Verity.

13:34.800 --> 13:39.080
Now ask your husband some difficult questions.

13:39.080 --> 13:43.760
Mrs. Seeker was afraid, but she spoke.

13:43.760 --> 13:45.520
Are you married?

13:45.520 --> 13:47.000
She asked.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.840
Of course I'm married.

13:48.840 --> 13:50.600
Replied, Mr. Seeker.

13:50.600 --> 13:52.480
You're my wife.

13:52.480 --> 13:54.440
He was angry.

13:54.440 --> 13:58.960
But do you love me?

13:58.960 --> 14:01.200
Asked Mrs. Seeker.

14:01.200 --> 14:04.000
Mr. Seeker looked at his wife.

14:04.000 --> 14:06.600
She waited.

14:06.600 --> 14:10.320
Now, he said slowly.

14:10.320 --> 14:13.400
Now, I don't love you.

14:13.400 --> 14:16.280
I'll have another woman.

14:16.280 --> 14:19.200
Oh, said Mrs. Seeker.

14:19.200 --> 14:20.840
Who do you love?

14:20.840 --> 14:22.040
Tell me the truth.

14:22.040 --> 14:23.320
I hate lies.

14:23.320 --> 14:25.320
Who do you love?

14:25.320 --> 14:27.840
Mrs. Seeker was crying.

14:27.840 --> 14:31.080
Mr. Seeker looked at his wife.

14:31.080 --> 14:33.640
I love anelyate.

14:33.640 --> 14:38.120
I love anelyate, he said.

14:38.120 --> 14:41.080
Oh, anelyate.

14:41.080 --> 14:44.080
But she's my best friend.

14:44.080 --> 14:46.840
Now you know the truth.

14:46.840 --> 14:50.440
Yes, that's the truth.

14:50.440 --> 14:57.440
What shall I do now?

14:57.440 --> 15:01.720
Inspector Sack came to the laboratory on Monday afternoon.

15:01.720 --> 15:05.080
His boss, the chief inspector, came too.

15:05.080 --> 15:09.040
They brought some criminals with them.

15:09.040 --> 15:11.240
Good afternoon, professor.

15:11.240 --> 15:13.360
Shouted Inspector Sack.

15:13.360 --> 15:16.360
This is my boss, the chief inspector.

15:16.360 --> 15:18.520
And these are the criminals.

15:18.520 --> 15:20.240
They are murderers.

15:20.240 --> 15:21.760
They are thieves.

15:21.760 --> 15:24.360
And they are liars.

15:24.360 --> 15:30.120
But today, said Professor Verity, they will tell the truth.

15:30.120 --> 15:31.760
Shall we begin?

15:31.760 --> 15:35.040
Said the chief inspector quietly.

15:35.040 --> 15:36.880
Yes, let's begin.

15:36.880 --> 15:38.040
Come on.

15:38.040 --> 15:40.320
Shouted Inspector Sack.

15:40.320 --> 15:43.600
Inspector Sack sat in the questioner's chair.

15:43.600 --> 15:47.200
The first criminal sat in the truth speaker's chair.

15:47.200 --> 15:49.520
Inspector Sack spoke.

15:49.520 --> 15:54.040
Did you take money from the car of Senor Cavallio?

15:54.040 --> 15:55.760
He asked.

15:55.760 --> 15:58.680
Yes, I took the money.

15:58.680 --> 16:00.320
Said the criminal.

16:00.320 --> 16:01.480
Guilty.

16:01.480 --> 16:03.440
Shouted Inspector Sack.

16:03.440 --> 16:05.760
Five years in prison.

16:05.760 --> 16:07.960
Next criminal.

16:07.960 --> 16:12.040
The next criminal sat in the truth speaker's chair.

16:12.040 --> 16:17.080
Did you take diamonds from the house of Senorita Regia?

16:17.080 --> 16:19.440
Asked Inspector Sack.

16:19.440 --> 16:21.480
Yes, I did.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.080
Said the criminal.

16:23.080 --> 16:24.120
Guilty.

16:24.120 --> 16:25.840
Shouted the inspector.

16:25.840 --> 16:28.160
Ten years in prison.

16:28.160 --> 16:29.080
Next criminal.

16:32.560 --> 16:34.680
The next criminal came in.

16:34.680 --> 16:37.920
He sat in the truth speaker's chair.

16:37.920 --> 16:41.400
Did you kill Senor Regia?

16:41.400 --> 16:43.880
Asked Inspector Sack.

16:43.880 --> 16:46.360
The criminal was silent.

16:46.360 --> 16:48.600
Then he spoke.

16:48.600 --> 16:50.960
Yes, I did.

16:50.960 --> 16:52.960
He said.

16:52.960 --> 16:54.960
That was the truth.

16:54.960 --> 16:56.080
Guilty.

16:56.080 --> 16:57.960
Shouted Inspector Sack.

16:57.960 --> 16:59.840
Twenty years.

16:59.840 --> 17:01.680
Next.

17:01.680 --> 17:04.880
All the criminals sat in the truth speaker's chair.

17:04.880 --> 17:07.080
They all told the truth.

17:07.080 --> 17:09.600
One of them was innocent.

17:09.600 --> 17:11.800
You are not guilty.

17:11.800 --> 17:13.440
Said Inspector Sack.

17:13.440 --> 17:16.240
You can go home.

17:16.240 --> 17:18.480
Inspector Sack was pleased.

17:18.480 --> 17:20.760
Professor Verity was pleased.

17:20.760 --> 17:23.040
The Chief Inspector was pleased.

17:23.040 --> 17:25.280
Good work, Sack.

17:25.280 --> 17:27.200
Said the Chief Inspector.

17:27.200 --> 17:29.120
Very good work.

17:29.120 --> 17:31.040
Thank you, sir.

17:31.040 --> 17:32.840
Said Inspector Sack.

17:32.840 --> 17:35.160
We are fighting crime, sir.

17:35.160 --> 17:37.760
The throat machine is helping us.

17:37.760 --> 17:42.160
There are no more criminals for us, sir.

17:42.160 --> 17:43.800
Inspector Sack smiled.

17:43.800 --> 17:45.440
He was happy.

17:45.440 --> 17:48.200
Yes, Inspector Sack.

17:48.200 --> 17:50.200
No more criminals.

17:50.200 --> 17:53.000
No more work.

17:53.000 --> 17:56.240
No more work for me, sir.

17:56.240 --> 17:57.400
Yes.

17:57.400 --> 18:00.760
We don't need you now, Inspector Sack.

18:00.760 --> 18:03.120
I haven't got a job.

18:03.120 --> 18:08.960
What shall I do now?

18:08.960 --> 18:11.000
It was Monday evening.

18:11.000 --> 18:14.160
Doctor Simple came to the laboratory.

18:14.160 --> 18:16.120
Another man came with him.

18:16.120 --> 18:18.120
The other man was a spy.

18:18.120 --> 18:20.840
Good evening, Professor.

18:20.840 --> 18:22.840
Said Doctor Simple.

18:22.840 --> 18:24.680
Good evening, Doctor Simple.

18:24.680 --> 18:26.520
Said the Professor.

18:26.520 --> 18:28.080
Everything is ready.

18:28.080 --> 18:31.080
Good, said Doctor Simple.

18:31.080 --> 18:33.320
This spy is dangerous.

18:33.320 --> 18:34.920
He is an enemy.

18:34.920 --> 18:36.840
I will be his questioner.

18:36.840 --> 18:39.000
He will be the truth speaker.

18:39.000 --> 18:41.840
He will tell the truth.

18:41.840 --> 18:44.280
The Professor went to the controls.

18:44.280 --> 18:47.080
Doctor Simple sat in the questioner's chair.

18:47.080 --> 18:50.600
The spy sat in the truth speaker's chair.

18:50.600 --> 18:52.200
What is your name?

18:52.200 --> 18:54.360
Asked Doctor Simple.

18:54.360 --> 18:57.240
My name is Horaville Wein.

18:57.240 --> 18:59.240
Said the spy.

18:59.240 --> 19:00.920
Where are you from?

19:00.920 --> 19:02.840
Asked Doctor Simple.

19:02.840 --> 19:05.000
I am from Russia.

19:05.000 --> 19:06.760
Said the spy.

19:06.760 --> 19:08.760
The spy smiled.

19:08.760 --> 19:11.240
Doctor Simple looked at the Professor.

19:11.240 --> 19:13.720
Doctor Simple was pleased.

19:13.720 --> 19:15.800
Excellent, Professor Verity.

19:15.800 --> 19:17.640
Said Doctor Simple.

19:17.640 --> 19:19.480
Lime is telling the truth.

19:19.480 --> 19:22.520
He will tell me everything.

19:22.520 --> 19:24.120
Professor Verity was happy.

19:27.080 --> 19:28.680
Doctor Simple looked at Lime.

19:30.200 --> 19:31.240
Are you a spy?

19:32.040 --> 19:32.600
He asked.

19:33.800 --> 19:36.040
Yes, I am a spy.

19:36.680 --> 19:38.600
I am an important spy.

19:39.320 --> 19:39.880
Said Lime.

19:40.760 --> 19:44.520
Do you know the secret of the new military aircraft?

19:45.240 --> 19:45.800
He asked.

19:46.920 --> 19:48.360
How the lime smiled.

19:49.400 --> 19:50.920
Yes, he said.

19:51.960 --> 19:55.880
I know the secret of the new military aircraft.

19:55.880 --> 19:57.720
And my government knows too.

19:59.080 --> 19:59.400
Ahh!

20:00.280 --> 20:01.800
Cried Doctor Simple.

20:01.800 --> 20:04.360
The truth machine is wonderful.

20:04.360 --> 20:06.440
The spy is telling me everything.

20:07.480 --> 20:09.480
But I have another secret.

20:10.280 --> 20:10.840
Said Lime.

20:11.800 --> 20:13.080
He looked at Doctor Simple.

20:13.880 --> 20:15.480
He looked at Professor Verity.

20:16.520 --> 20:18.040
Another secret.

20:18.040 --> 20:19.480
Cried Doctor Simple.

20:19.480 --> 20:21.720
Tell me, tell me, tell me the truth.

20:23.320 --> 20:24.760
My secret is this.

20:25.560 --> 20:26.600
Said Harvey Lime.

20:27.400 --> 20:29.240
I never tell the truth.

20:29.960 --> 20:31.720
I always tell lies.

20:32.840 --> 20:33.480
He smiled.

20:35.480 --> 20:36.280
What do you mean?

20:37.640 --> 20:39.080
That's the truth.

20:39.160 --> 20:40.840
I always tell lies.

20:43.400 --> 20:45.080
Is Lime telling the truth?

20:45.960 --> 20:47.400
Or is he lying?

21:09.560 --> 21:11.080
What do you mean?

21:13.080 --> 21:13.800
Chapter 4.

21:14.840 --> 21:15.400
Tuesday.

21:15.880 --> 21:17.080
An important meeting.

21:18.680 --> 21:20.680
There was a hotel near the laboratory.

21:21.560 --> 21:23.080
Mrs. Seeker was staying there.

21:23.960 --> 21:27.160
Inspector Sack and Doctor Simple were staying there too.

21:28.200 --> 21:33.160
Mrs. Seeker, Inspector Sack and Doctor Simple were eating breakfast together.

21:34.600 --> 21:36.600
I know the truth about my husband.

21:37.400 --> 21:39.080
Now I am very unhappy.

21:39.880 --> 21:40.840
Said Mrs. Seeker.

21:42.200 --> 21:44.760
I know the truth about my criminals.

21:45.480 --> 21:47.320
Now I haven't got a job.

21:48.040 --> 21:49.160
Said Inspector Sack.

21:50.200 --> 21:52.440
I know the truth about my spy.

21:53.320 --> 21:54.520
What shall I do now?

21:55.160 --> 21:56.120
Said Doctor Simple.

21:57.640 --> 21:59.080
Mrs. Seeker was crying.

22:00.040 --> 22:02.440
I don't like the truth, machine.

22:02.520 --> 22:03.000
She said.

22:04.040 --> 22:07.000
Inspector Sack and Doctor Simple agreed with her.

22:08.120 --> 22:10.520
Inspector Sack shouted in a loud voice.

22:11.640 --> 22:14.440
We paid the professor a lot of money.

22:15.000 --> 22:15.480
He said.

22:16.520 --> 22:19.240
Mrs. Seeker and Doctor Simple agreed with him.

22:20.520 --> 22:23.080
Doctor Simple spoke quietly and slowly.

22:24.520 --> 22:27.160
Professor Verity is a criminal.

22:27.800 --> 22:28.280
He said.

22:29.320 --> 22:32.360
Mrs. Seeker and Inspector Sack agreed with him.

22:33.320 --> 22:35.480
I'm going to say Professor Verity.

22:35.880 --> 22:36.920
Said Mrs. Seeker.

22:37.640 --> 22:39.080
I shall come with you.

22:39.640 --> 22:41.000
Shouted Inspector Sack.

22:42.040 --> 22:43.640
A good idea.

22:44.280 --> 22:45.960
Said Doctor Simple slowly.

22:46.760 --> 22:47.960
I shall come too.

22:49.640 --> 22:53.880
Mrs. Seeker, Inspector Sack and Doctor Simple left the hotel.

22:54.680 --> 22:56.520
They wanted to see Professor Verity.

22:57.400 --> 22:58.680
They went to the laboratory.

23:02.440 --> 23:04.440
I shall come with you.

23:12.440 --> 23:13.320
Chapter 5.

23:14.280 --> 23:15.640
At the laboratory again.

23:17.400 --> 23:22.520
Soon Mrs. Seeker, Inspector Sack and Doctor Simple were at the laboratory.

23:23.640 --> 23:26.280
Oh, I hate you, Professor Verity.

23:27.080 --> 23:28.200
Cried Mrs. Seeker.

23:28.840 --> 23:31.240
I want my money back, Professor.

23:31.720 --> 23:33.000
Shouted Inspector Sack.

23:33.720 --> 23:35.480
You're a criminal, Verity.

23:36.120 --> 23:37.160
Said Doctor Simple.

23:38.600 --> 23:41.480
Professor Verity looked at his first three clients.

23:42.920 --> 23:44.600
Fools, he said.

23:45.320 --> 23:46.600
You are fools.

23:47.240 --> 23:48.760
You wanted the truth.

23:48.760 --> 23:50.520
I gave you the truth.

23:50.520 --> 23:53.000
The truth machine gave you the truth.

23:53.960 --> 23:54.360
Truth?

23:54.920 --> 23:56.360
Said Mrs. Seeker.

23:56.360 --> 23:57.960
But now I am unhappy.

23:59.000 --> 23:59.560
Throws?

24:00.200 --> 24:01.960
Shouted Inspector Sack.

24:01.960 --> 24:04.040
But now I haven't got a job.

24:05.560 --> 24:06.040
Truth?

24:06.600 --> 24:07.560
Said Doctor Simple.

24:08.120 --> 24:09.480
But what is the truth?

24:10.920 --> 24:12.040
What is the truth?

24:12.680 --> 24:13.800
Said Professor Verity.

24:14.520 --> 24:15.480
Let me tell you.

24:16.280 --> 24:20.200
Mrs. Seeker, you hate lies and I gave you the truth.

24:20.200 --> 24:22.360
Your husband loves Anne Elliot.

24:22.360 --> 24:23.400
That is the truth.

24:24.120 --> 24:26.840
Inspector, the professor went on.

24:26.840 --> 24:28.360
You hate crime.

24:28.360 --> 24:30.600
I put your criminals in prison.

24:30.600 --> 24:31.720
That is the truth.

24:32.680 --> 24:33.560
Simple.

24:33.560 --> 24:34.440
Said the professor.

24:35.000 --> 24:36.120
You fight for peace.

24:36.760 --> 24:38.040
I helped you.

24:38.040 --> 24:39.320
That is the truth.

24:40.600 --> 24:41.800
The professor stopped.

24:42.440 --> 24:43.480
Then he spoke again.

24:44.760 --> 24:46.360
Fools, he said.

24:47.080 --> 24:47.880
Go home.

24:49.320 --> 24:52.200
Do you really hate lies, Professor Verity?

24:52.920 --> 24:53.960
Asked Mrs. Seeker.

24:54.840 --> 24:57.480
Do you really hate crime, Professor?

24:58.120 --> 24:59.400
Shouted Inspector Sack.

25:00.120 --> 25:02.040
And do you really fight for peace?

25:02.760 --> 25:03.800
Asked Doctor Simple.

25:04.680 --> 25:06.360
Yes, yes, yes.

25:06.920 --> 25:08.440
Cried Professor Verity.

25:08.440 --> 25:09.320
That's the truth.

25:10.840 --> 25:12.280
Then Doctor Simple spoke.

25:13.640 --> 25:14.600
We shall see.

25:15.400 --> 25:15.880
He said.

25:16.840 --> 25:19.720
Professor Verity will be the truth speaker.

25:24.440 --> 25:26.760
Why did you invent the truth machine?

25:28.280 --> 25:28.840
Success.

25:29.720 --> 25:30.680
I want success.

25:32.120 --> 25:33.800
What do you really want?

25:35.560 --> 25:35.880
Money.

25:36.680 --> 25:37.400
I want money.

25:39.000 --> 25:40.680
What do you really want?

25:42.360 --> 25:42.680
Power.

25:43.640 --> 25:44.440
I want power.

25:45.640 --> 25:48.360
You don't hate lies, Professor Verity.

25:48.360 --> 25:49.480
You want success?

25:50.360 --> 25:51.320
Said Mrs. Seeker.

25:52.200 --> 25:54.600
You don't hate crime, Professor.

25:54.600 --> 25:56.200
You want money.

25:56.840 --> 25:58.120
Shouted Inspector Sack.

25:58.920 --> 26:00.680
You don't want peace, Verity.

26:01.160 --> 26:02.280
You want power.

26:02.840 --> 26:03.880
Said Doctor Simple.

26:04.760 --> 26:05.080
Yes.

26:05.880 --> 26:07.080
Laugh, Professor Verity.

26:07.880 --> 26:09.000
You fools.

26:09.560 --> 26:11.080
You gave me success.

26:11.640 --> 26:13.080
You gave me money.

26:13.640 --> 26:15.080
You gave me power.

26:15.880 --> 26:19.560
Now I am successful, rich, and powerful.

26:20.120 --> 26:21.960
And that is the truth.

26:27.400 --> 26:28.680
Everybody was quiet.

26:29.720 --> 26:31.720
Then Inspector Sack took out his gun.

26:32.360 --> 26:33.800
Mrs. Seeker screamed.

26:34.440 --> 26:37.080
Inspector Sack shot Professor Verity.

26:37.880 --> 26:41.560
And Doctor Simple destroyed the truth machine.

26:49.560 --> 27:10.200
The truth machine was read by Stephen Pacey.

27:10.760 --> 27:15.480
And the recording produced by James Richardson at Studio AVP London.

27:17.560 --> 27:18.760
End of Side One.

27:19.560 --> 27:21.560
End of Side One.

27:40.360 --> 27:42.760
The Sky's the Limit by Norman Whitney.

27:43.480 --> 27:45.720
A Heinemann guided reader at beginner level.

27:46.680 --> 27:48.520
Copyright Heinemann International.

27:49.560 --> 27:51.400
First recorded 1982.

27:52.280 --> 27:54.360
This edition 1992.

28:03.400 --> 28:04.120
Chapter One.

28:05.320 --> 28:06.920
A new start for Max.

28:08.600 --> 28:10.520
Max Price was a happy man.

28:11.560 --> 28:15.720
He loved his wife Angela and his two children, Stephen and Juliet.

28:16.680 --> 28:19.720
Max and his family lived in a small, pleasant flat.

28:20.440 --> 28:23.240
They had many good friends and kind neighbors.

28:24.040 --> 28:26.840
Yes, the Price family was a happy family.

28:28.280 --> 28:30.840
But one day Max lost his job.

28:31.880 --> 28:33.480
The bad news came in a letter.

28:34.280 --> 28:36.040
The letter was short and clear.

28:36.840 --> 28:38.440
Max became very worried.

28:39.880 --> 28:41.480
What shall I do now?

28:41.480 --> 28:42.520
He said to his wife.

28:43.400 --> 28:45.000
I don't know, Max.

28:45.880 --> 28:47.800
I don't know, replied Angela.

28:48.760 --> 28:50.200
She was very worried too.

28:53.800 --> 28:55.320
Then Max became angry.

28:56.600 --> 28:58.120
Look at this letter, he said.

28:58.760 --> 29:00.280
They send me best wishes.

29:01.080 --> 29:02.920
I don't want best wishes.

29:02.920 --> 29:03.880
I want a job.

29:04.440 --> 29:06.040
I've got a wife and family.

29:07.720 --> 29:09.880
Don't worry, Max, said Angela.

29:10.520 --> 29:11.880
Everything will be all right.

29:13.080 --> 29:15.480
But who will give me a job now, Angela?

29:16.120 --> 29:17.240
I'm 37.

29:17.960 --> 29:20.040
And today, 37 is old.

29:21.000 --> 29:22.040
What are we going to do?

29:24.040 --> 29:27.160
Let's ask our friends and neighbors, said Angela.

29:28.360 --> 29:30.840
But they got no help from their friends and neighbors.

29:31.800 --> 29:33.480
Many people were looking for jobs.

29:34.280 --> 29:36.120
Life was difficult for everybody.

29:37.720 --> 29:39.880
Every morning, Max looked for a new job.

29:40.680 --> 29:43.320
Every afternoon, he came home without one.

29:44.200 --> 29:46.760
And every evening, he waited for the newspaper.

29:52.440 --> 29:53.960
Will there be a job tonight?

30:01.240 --> 30:05.240
Jobs, situations vacant, 12 to 14.

30:05.880 --> 30:07.880
Nothing here again.

30:10.520 --> 30:12.520
Angela, look at this.

30:15.400 --> 30:17.640
The sky's the limit.

30:18.360 --> 30:22.120
Join our new company and go to the top.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.480
Friendly people, good salaries,

30:26.040 --> 30:28.200
jobs for men and women of all ages,

30:29.160 --> 30:31.160
the star building, city center.

30:31.160 --> 30:33.160
Interviews every morning at nine.

30:35.640 --> 30:37.640
Mr. Lele, personnel manager,

30:38.840 --> 30:40.840
friendship services international,

30:41.480 --> 30:43.480
star building, city center.

30:46.520 --> 30:48.520
Friendship services international.

30:49.720 --> 30:51.720
It's a new company, said Max.

30:52.760 --> 30:54.760
What do you think, Angela?

30:55.960 --> 30:57.960
Go and see them.

30:57.960 --> 31:02.120
They need new people, men and women, and all ages, too.

31:04.600 --> 31:06.600
Yes, said Max.

31:07.800 --> 31:09.800
The star building.

31:10.360 --> 31:12.360
That's the new skyscraper in the city center.

31:13.320 --> 31:14.840
It's a big company, Angela.

31:15.800 --> 31:16.840
Very big.

31:17.800 --> 31:19.800
You can go in the morning, said Angela.

31:20.760 --> 31:22.280
I will, said Max.

31:23.480 --> 31:24.520
He was excited.

31:24.520 --> 31:26.520
I'll be there early.

31:26.520 --> 31:28.520
I'll be there at seven o'clock.

31:29.320 --> 31:31.320
I'll get a job, Angela.

31:31.320 --> 31:32.520
Don't worry.

31:33.720 --> 31:35.720
Early next morning, Max was at the star building.

31:36.920 --> 31:38.920
At nine o'clock, he had an interview

31:38.920 --> 31:41.720
with three men from friendship services international.

31:44.120 --> 31:46.120
What was your last job?

31:46.120 --> 31:48.120
Ask Mr. Lele, the personnel manager.

31:49.720 --> 31:51.720
I sold furniture.

31:51.720 --> 31:55.720
We don't need furniture salesmen here, said the second man, Mr. Crepe.

31:57.720 --> 31:59.720
But I'll learn a new job, said Max quickly.

31:59.720 --> 32:01.720
I'll work hard.

32:01.720 --> 32:03.720
Good.

32:03.720 --> 32:05.720
Said the third man, Mr. High Tower.

32:05.720 --> 32:09.720
We need new men, and we need hard workers.

32:09.720 --> 32:13.720
Mr. Price, said Max quickly.

32:13.720 --> 32:15.720
Very good, Price.

32:15.720 --> 32:17.720
Said Mr. High Tower.

32:17.720 --> 32:19.720
Be here tomorrow at eight thirty.

32:19.720 --> 32:23.720
We were now working for friendship services international.

32:25.720 --> 32:27.720
Now Max had a job.

32:27.720 --> 32:29.720
He ran home and told Angela the good news.

32:29.720 --> 32:31.720
This was a new start for Max.

32:47.720 --> 32:57.720
Chapter two, the ground floor.

32:57.720 --> 33:03.720
The next day, Max went to his new job.

33:03.720 --> 33:07.720
His office was on the ground floor of the star building.

33:07.720 --> 33:09.720
Many new people started work that day.

33:09.720 --> 33:11.720
One of them was Frank Stedman.

33:11.720 --> 33:13.720
He became Max's friend.

33:13.720 --> 33:18.720
Their office was large and busy, but everybody was very friendly.

33:18.720 --> 33:23.720
Max and Frank liked everybody, and they did their work well.

33:23.720 --> 33:27.720
I like it here, Max, said Frank one day.

33:27.720 --> 33:31.720
We've got good jobs at friendship services international.

33:31.720 --> 33:33.720
Yes, said Max.

33:33.720 --> 33:35.720
I like it here too.

33:35.720 --> 33:37.720
So the two men were very happy.

33:37.720 --> 33:41.720
Every lunchtime they had drinks and sandwiches with their new friends.

33:41.720 --> 33:44.720
In the evenings they went to parties with them.

33:44.720 --> 33:48.720
Max and Frank often took their wives and children to the parties.

33:48.720 --> 33:50.720
Max was pleased.

33:50.720 --> 33:53.720
And Angela was pleased too.

33:53.720 --> 33:56.720
Max now had a good salary.

33:56.720 --> 34:00.720
So he and Angela bought lots of new furniture for their flat.

34:00.720 --> 34:05.720
They bought a color television, a hi-fi, and many other things.

34:05.720 --> 34:08.720
Angela bought some new clothes.

34:08.720 --> 34:13.720
Angela bought some new clothes, and the children had lots of new toys.

34:13.720 --> 34:17.720
The Price family was happy again.

34:17.720 --> 34:21.720
You're rich, said Angela, one day to Max.

34:21.720 --> 34:23.720
Max laughed.

34:23.720 --> 34:26.720
No, not yet Angela, he said.

34:26.720 --> 34:29.720
But perhaps I'll be rich one day.

34:29.720 --> 34:33.720
Let's drink to your new job, said Angela.

34:33.720 --> 34:36.720
Yes, agreed Max.

34:36.720 --> 34:38.720
Let's drink to my new employer.

34:38.720 --> 34:42.720
Let's drink to Friendship Services International.

34:42.720 --> 34:44.720
Cheers, Angela.

34:44.720 --> 34:47.720
Cheers, Max, said Angela.

34:51.720 --> 34:55.720
The work at Friendship Services International was hard.

34:55.720 --> 34:59.720
Every day Max and Frank received lots of letters.

34:59.720 --> 35:02.720
These letters wanted FSI products.

35:02.720 --> 35:05.720
But FSI products had no names.

35:05.720 --> 35:08.720
They only had numbers and letters.

35:08.720 --> 35:14.720
X3Ys, L7Ks, A5Qs.

35:14.720 --> 35:18.720
What did these strange numbers and letters mean?

35:18.720 --> 35:21.720
Max and Frank did not know.

35:21.720 --> 35:25.720
Each day they opened hundreds of these orders.

35:25.720 --> 35:27.720
They put the orders into groups.

35:27.720 --> 35:32.720
One group for X products, one group for L products,

35:32.720 --> 35:35.720
and one group for A products.

35:35.720 --> 35:38.720
The orders came from all over the world.

35:38.720 --> 35:42.720
Some of the orders were very big.

35:42.720 --> 35:46.720
We're working very hard, said Max, to Frank one day.

35:46.720 --> 35:49.720
Yes, replied Frank.

35:49.720 --> 35:53.720
Letters, letters, letters, hundreds of them.

35:53.720 --> 35:55.720
What do they mean, Max?

35:55.720 --> 35:57.720
What do they want?

35:57.720 --> 36:00.720
What are they asking for?

36:00.720 --> 36:03.720
I don't know, said Max.

36:03.720 --> 36:06.720
Don't ask so many questions, Frank.

36:06.720 --> 36:09.720
Okay, said Frank.

36:09.720 --> 36:11.720
Okay.

36:11.720 --> 36:19.720
Later that day, a memo came from their boss, Mr. B. Creep.

36:19.720 --> 36:21.720
Confidential.

36:21.720 --> 36:24.720
Date July 1st from B. Creep.

36:24.720 --> 36:28.720
2, M price and F. Stedman.

36:28.720 --> 36:32.720
Please see me now in my office, 5th floor.

36:32.720 --> 36:40.720
Copy to M high tower.

36:40.720 --> 36:43.720
Please sit down, gentlemen.

36:43.720 --> 36:49.720
I have some news for you.

36:49.720 --> 36:51.720
We like your work.

36:51.720 --> 36:54.720
You'll be coming up to the 5th floor.

36:54.720 --> 36:56.720
Well done, Frank.

36:56.720 --> 36:59.720
Well done, Max.

37:11.720 --> 37:13.720
Chapter 3.

37:13.720 --> 37:16.720
The 5th floor.

37:16.720 --> 37:20.720
Max and Frank now worked on the 5th floor.

37:20.720 --> 37:24.720
There were two other men and one secretary in their new office.

37:24.720 --> 37:26.720
The office was quiet.

37:26.720 --> 37:29.720
Its furniture was modern and expensive.

37:29.720 --> 37:33.720
The secretary had a dictaphone and an electric typewriter.

37:33.720 --> 37:36.720
The four men had large desks.

37:36.720 --> 37:40.720
One day, Max and Frank looked down on the street below.

37:40.720 --> 37:44.720
There was a lot of noise and traffic in the street.

37:44.720 --> 37:49.720
Max and Frank remembered their friends on the ground floor.

37:49.720 --> 37:52.720
They were good friends, said Frank.

37:52.720 --> 37:58.720
Yes, said Max, but now we've got new friends on the 5th floor.

37:58.720 --> 38:05.720
But remember the parties and the friendship on the ground floor, said Frank?

38:05.720 --> 38:14.720
Yes, said Max, but Frank, the salaries on the 5th floor are better.

38:14.720 --> 38:17.720
Max now had more money.

38:17.720 --> 38:21.720
Let's buy a new house, he said to Angela.

38:21.720 --> 38:24.720
But I like it here, said Angela.

38:24.720 --> 38:27.720
And the children like it here too.

38:27.720 --> 38:33.720
But Angela, said Max, I now work on the 5th floor at Friendship Services International.

38:33.720 --> 38:35.720
My salary is bigger.

38:35.720 --> 38:38.720
5th floor people don't live in flats.

38:38.720 --> 38:40.720
They live in houses.

38:40.720 --> 38:43.720
But Max said Angela.

38:43.720 --> 38:45.720
All our friends live here.

38:45.720 --> 38:48.720
And the children go to school here.

38:48.720 --> 38:51.720
And our flat is lovely now.

38:51.720 --> 38:53.720
Max became angry.

38:53.720 --> 38:56.720
We are going to move, Angela.

38:56.720 --> 39:00.720
We are going to move next week.

39:00.720 --> 39:03.720
All right, said Angela.

39:03.720 --> 39:09.720
She smiled, but she was unhappy.

39:09.720 --> 39:14.720
The next week, Max and Angela moved to a new house.

39:14.720 --> 39:17.720
But Frank's dead man and his wife did not move.

39:17.720 --> 39:20.720
We like our flat, said Frank.

39:20.720 --> 39:22.720
All our friends are near us.

39:22.720 --> 39:24.720
And the children like their school.

39:24.720 --> 39:27.720
No, I shall not move, Max.

39:27.720 --> 39:33.720
Max said nothing.

39:33.720 --> 39:36.720
Max and Frank worked hard in their 5th floor office.

39:36.720 --> 39:41.720
They received orders to Friendship Services International and priced them.

39:42.720 --> 39:47.720
For example, there was an order for 5,000 M5Bs.

39:47.720 --> 39:49.720
The prices were in a book.

39:49.720 --> 39:52.720
1M5B cost $10.

39:52.720 --> 40:01.720
So 5,000 M5Bs cost 5,000 times 10 equals $50,000.

40:01.720 --> 40:07.720
But Max and Frank still did not understand M5B.

40:07.720 --> 40:11.720
What's an M5B, asked Frank?

40:11.720 --> 40:20.720
I don't know, said Max.

40:20.720 --> 40:23.720
Now their boss was Mr. M. Heitauer.

40:23.720 --> 40:27.720
His office was on the 10th floor of the star building.

40:27.720 --> 40:32.720
He came down every day at 5 o'clock and spoke to Max and Frank.

40:32.720 --> 40:35.720
Your work is excellent, gentlemen.

40:35.720 --> 40:39.720
Said Mr. Heitauer one day, excellent.

40:39.720 --> 40:42.720
Thank you, Mr. Heitauer, said Max.

40:42.720 --> 40:44.720
Call me Mort, please.

40:44.720 --> 40:46.720
Said Mr. Heitauer.

40:46.720 --> 40:47.720
Thank you, Mort.

40:47.720 --> 40:49.720
I will, said Max.

40:49.720 --> 40:52.720
But Frank said nothing.

40:52.720 --> 40:55.720
One day, Mr. Heitauer came down early.

40:55.720 --> 40:58.720
Max and Frank were alone in their office.

40:58.720 --> 41:00.720
Anything wrong, Mort?

41:00.720 --> 41:03.720
Asked Max?

41:03.720 --> 41:06.720
No, nothing is wrong.

41:06.720 --> 41:08.720
Good news, gentlemen.

41:08.720 --> 41:14.720
We are going to open a new department on the 10th floor.

41:14.720 --> 41:18.720
And you will be the bosses.

41:18.720 --> 41:22.720
Thanks, Mort. That's great news.

41:34.720 --> 41:36.720
Chapter 4.

41:36.720 --> 41:39.720
Higher and higher.

41:39.720 --> 41:43.720
The 10th floor office was large and comfortable.

41:43.720 --> 41:46.720
Max and Frank were the only two men in it.

41:46.720 --> 41:50.720
They had large desks and large telephones.

41:50.720 --> 41:52.720
There was a secretary, too.

41:52.720 --> 41:55.720
She also had a large desk.

41:55.720 --> 41:59.720
One morning, Max and Frank looked down on the city below.

41:59.720 --> 42:01.720
It was a long way.

42:01.720 --> 42:05.720
The people and the cars were very small.

42:05.720 --> 42:08.720
It's very high, Frank, said Max.

42:08.720 --> 42:11.720
I like it up here.

42:11.720 --> 42:14.720
It's too high, Max, said Frank.

42:14.720 --> 42:16.720
I liked it on the ground floor.

42:16.720 --> 42:19.720
There's too much work up here.

42:19.720 --> 42:22.720
But we must work, said Max.

42:22.720 --> 42:24.720
This is Friendship Services International.

42:24.720 --> 42:26.720
It's a good company.

42:26.720 --> 42:28.720
We must work.

42:29.720 --> 42:31.720
Max worked very hard.

42:31.720 --> 42:36.720
He often worked late in the office.

42:36.720 --> 42:39.720
One evening, Max came home early.

42:39.720 --> 42:41.720
Angela was pleased.

42:41.720 --> 42:43.720
Hello, Max.

42:43.720 --> 42:45.720
You're early tonight.

42:45.720 --> 42:48.720
I'm cooking your favorite meal.

42:48.720 --> 42:51.720
I'm sorry, Angela, said Max.

42:51.720 --> 42:53.720
I must go out again in a few minutes.

42:53.720 --> 42:56.720
I've got an important business dinner.

42:56.720 --> 42:59.720
Oh, please stay, said Angela.

42:59.720 --> 43:02.720
I don't see you a lot these days.

43:02.720 --> 43:05.720
And the children don't see you at all.

43:05.720 --> 43:09.720
I'm sorry, Angela, said Max, but it's an important dinner.

43:09.720 --> 43:11.720
I must go.

43:11.720 --> 43:13.720
Goodbye.

43:13.720 --> 43:15.720
Goodbye, Max.

43:15.720 --> 43:18.720
Good luck.

43:18.720 --> 43:21.720
Oh, Max thought Angela to herself.

43:21.720 --> 43:24.720
You are becoming a different man.

43:24.720 --> 43:27.720
And the children don't know you now.

43:27.720 --> 43:30.720
You are a stranger in our home.

43:30.720 --> 43:33.720
It was a very important business dinner.

43:33.720 --> 43:35.720
Max and Frank were there.

43:35.720 --> 43:39.720
They met many foreign customers of Friendship Services International.

43:39.720 --> 43:42.720
But Mort Heitauer wasn't at the dinner.

43:42.720 --> 43:44.720
Where's Heitauer tonight?

43:44.720 --> 43:46.720
Asked Frank.

43:46.720 --> 43:47.720
Mort?

43:47.720 --> 43:50.720
I don't know, said Max.

43:50.720 --> 43:52.720
He wasn't well this morning.

43:52.720 --> 43:55.720
What's the office early?

43:55.720 --> 43:58.720
Max and Frank talked to the dinner guests.

43:58.720 --> 44:01.720
They came from all over the world.

44:01.720 --> 44:02.720
They were rich.

44:02.720 --> 44:05.720
They ate and drank a lot.

44:05.720 --> 44:10.720
We like Friendship Services International, said an African guest.

44:10.720 --> 44:11.720
Oh, yes.

44:11.720 --> 44:15.720
Your products are very good, said an Asian guest.

44:15.720 --> 44:17.720
Then Max asked a question.

44:17.720 --> 44:20.720
He spoke to an American guest.

44:20.720 --> 44:23.720
Excuse me, he said.

44:23.720 --> 44:26.720
Yes, said the American.

44:26.720 --> 44:30.720
I've read your letters to FSI, said Max.

44:30.720 --> 44:32.720
I've seen your orders.

44:32.720 --> 44:36.720
For example, you ordered 300 S6Ts.

44:36.720 --> 44:39.720
That's right, said the American.

44:39.720 --> 44:42.720
300 S6Ts.

44:42.720 --> 44:44.720
They were excellent.

44:45.720 --> 44:50.720
But what is S6T, asked Max?

44:50.720 --> 44:52.720
What your orders mean?

44:52.720 --> 44:55.720
I don't understand them.

44:55.720 --> 44:57.720
The American laughed.

44:57.720 --> 45:00.720
Oh, our orders.

45:00.720 --> 45:02.720
Don't worry.

45:02.720 --> 45:05.720
He said, you'll earn one day.

45:05.720 --> 45:08.720
But not now, Max.

45:08.720 --> 45:11.720
The other guests laughed too.

45:12.720 --> 45:15.720
Max and Frank were going to ask another question.

45:15.720 --> 45:24.720
But at that moment, there was an urgent message for Max.

45:24.720 --> 45:27.720
From FSI headquarters.

45:27.720 --> 45:29.720
High tower dead.

45:29.720 --> 45:31.720
Move to his job tomorrow.

45:31.720 --> 45:34.720
Fifteenth floor.

45:34.720 --> 45:37.720
I've got Mort's job, Frank.

45:37.720 --> 45:41.720
I'm on the fifteenth floor.

45:41.720 --> 45:43.720
Oh, Max.

45:43.720 --> 45:45.720
Be careful.

45:57.720 --> 45:59.720
Chapter five.

45:59.720 --> 46:02.720
An important man.

46:03.720 --> 46:08.720
The office on the fifteenth floor had every modern office machine.

46:08.720 --> 46:14.720
There was also a beautiful carpet on the floor and modern paintings on the walls.

46:14.720 --> 46:18.720
Max didn't like the paintings, but they were expensive.

46:18.720 --> 46:20.720
That pleased Max.

46:20.720 --> 46:26.720
From the window, Max looked out at the other skyscrapers in the city.

46:26.720 --> 46:27.720
Yes, thought Max.

46:27.720 --> 46:30.720
I'm an important man now.

46:30.720 --> 46:33.720
I'm rising higher in FSI.

46:33.720 --> 46:36.720
I'm rising higher in the star building.

46:36.720 --> 46:39.720
And I've got a beautiful secretary.

46:39.720 --> 46:41.720
It was true.

46:41.720 --> 46:44.720
Max's secretary was called Donna Lot.

46:44.720 --> 46:46.720
She was beautiful.

46:46.720 --> 46:50.720
She liked Max, and Max liked her.

46:50.720 --> 46:53.720
They did a lot of work together.

46:53.720 --> 46:56.720
Max and Donna often worked late.

46:56.720 --> 46:59.720
Sometimes they went to restaurants after work.

46:59.720 --> 47:03.720
One evening, Max telephoned Angela from a restaurant.

47:03.720 --> 47:06.720
Hello, Angela Darling, he said.

47:06.720 --> 47:08.720
It's Max here.

47:08.720 --> 47:10.720
Max said Angela.

47:10.720 --> 47:12.720
Where are you?

47:12.720 --> 47:14.720
We're waiting for you.

47:14.720 --> 47:16.720
It's nine o'clock.

47:16.720 --> 47:19.720
I'm in the office, said Max.

47:19.720 --> 47:21.720
I'm working late.

47:21.720 --> 47:24.720
But Max said Angela.

47:24.720 --> 47:26.720
It's Steven's birthday.

47:26.720 --> 47:28.720
He's waiting for you.

47:29.720 --> 47:31.720
Oh, said Max.

47:31.720 --> 47:33.720
I forgot.

47:33.720 --> 47:35.720
I'm sorry, Angela.

47:35.720 --> 47:37.720
I'll see him tomorrow.

47:37.720 --> 47:41.720
Tomorrow, Max, said Angela.

47:41.720 --> 47:43.720
Tomorrow?

47:43.720 --> 47:45.720
Oh, Max.

47:45.720 --> 47:48.720
Your work is more important to you than your home.

47:48.720 --> 47:51.720
Angela was angry.

47:51.720 --> 47:53.720
She put the phone down.

47:53.720 --> 47:55.720
Max rang her again.

47:55.720 --> 48:01.720
But Angela did not answer.

48:01.720 --> 48:04.720
Max did not see his son the next day.

48:04.720 --> 48:06.720
He went to work early.

48:06.720 --> 48:08.720
There were many letters for him.

48:08.720 --> 48:11.720
Max and Donna worked hard.

48:11.720 --> 48:14.720
Do you understand these letters?

48:14.720 --> 48:16.720
Max asked Donna.

48:16.720 --> 48:18.720
What do you mean, Max?

48:18.720 --> 48:20.720
She replied.

48:20.720 --> 48:24.720
Do you understand these orders, said Max?

48:24.720 --> 48:27.720
What is a B5R?

48:27.720 --> 48:30.720
What is a G9Q?

48:30.720 --> 48:32.720
Do you know?

48:32.720 --> 48:35.720
Donna spoke slowly.

48:35.720 --> 48:39.720
They're secret things, she said.

48:39.720 --> 48:41.720
I know, said Max.

48:41.720 --> 48:44.720
But why are they secret?

48:44.720 --> 48:47.720
I don't know, Max, said Donna.

48:47.720 --> 48:49.720
Then she smiled.

48:49.720 --> 48:52.720
But you can find out.

48:52.720 --> 48:54.720
How? asked Max.

48:54.720 --> 48:57.720
How can I find out?

48:57.720 --> 49:02.720
You can become a director of the company, said Donna.

49:02.720 --> 49:04.720
Max laughed.

49:04.720 --> 49:07.720
Me? Max Price?

49:07.720 --> 49:11.720
A director of Friendship Services International?

49:11.720 --> 49:13.720
It's impossible.

49:13.720 --> 49:16.720
It isn't impossible, said Donna.

49:16.720 --> 49:19.720
I can help you.

49:19.720 --> 49:21.720
You said Max?

49:21.720 --> 49:23.720
He was surprised.

49:23.720 --> 49:27.720
How can you help me?

49:27.720 --> 49:29.720
I have a cousin.

49:29.720 --> 49:32.720
He is a director of FSI.

49:32.720 --> 49:35.720
But will he help me, Donna?

49:35.720 --> 49:39.720
Yes, of course he'll help you, Max.

49:39.720 --> 49:42.720
You'll be a director too.

49:42.720 --> 49:44.720
Thanks, Donna.

49:44.720 --> 49:46.720
Thanks a lot.

49:49.720 --> 49:52.720
Thank you very much.

50:20.720 --> 50:25.720
They were talking about sales and profits.

50:25.720 --> 50:29.720
X-5B's are selling well, said one man.

50:29.720 --> 50:34.720
And we're making good profits on V3Q's, said another man.

50:34.720 --> 50:37.720
Max looked at his papers.

50:37.720 --> 50:41.720
See, seven T's are selling well, he said.

50:41.720 --> 50:46.720
And we're making good profits on U-8Ds.

50:46.720 --> 50:51.520
said somebody. Thank you, Mr. Price!"

50:51.520 --> 51:00.560
Everybody smiled at Max. Max smiled at everybody. But Max still did not understand. C-7-T's

51:00.560 --> 51:09.160
and U-8-D's were selling well, but what were they? Max didn't know.

51:09.160 --> 51:16.200
Now Max was very busy. He always arrived home very late. One evening he arrived home

51:16.200 --> 51:23.480
about midnight. He was very tired. But Angela and the children were not there. Max looked

51:23.480 --> 51:27.380
in all the rooms. There was nobody.

51:27.380 --> 51:37.600
"'Angela!' shouted Max. "'Where are you? Stephen! Juliet! Where are you? I'm home! It's

51:37.600 --> 51:39.600
daddy!'

51:39.600 --> 51:46.320
But there was no answer. Max went into the bedroom again. Then he found a letter. It

51:46.320 --> 51:55.360
was on the bed. Max looked at the envelope. Suddenly he felt sad. Suddenly he knew. He

51:55.360 --> 51:58.600
opened the envelope and read the letter.

51:58.600 --> 52:02.240
"'Yes, it was from Angela.'

52:03.240 --> 52:12.960
"'Dear Max, I'm going away with the children. Goodbye, Max. We will think of you. Goodbye.

52:12.960 --> 52:22.880
All my love, Angela. P.S. Good luck on the board of directors."

52:22.880 --> 52:30.680
Now Max had no family. He was sad and lonely. So he traveled. He traveled for friendship

52:30.680 --> 52:38.040
services international. He traveled all over the five continents. Europe, Africa, Asia,

52:38.040 --> 52:45.440
America, Australia. Max was very good at his work. His customers liked him.

52:45.440 --> 52:51.560
Max took letters and papers to each customer. Many of the customers were scientists. The

52:51.560 --> 52:59.840
papers were top secret. Max did not understand them. He was not a scientist. He showed the

52:59.840 --> 53:05.880
papers to customers in many foreign countries. The customers read the documents. Then they

53:05.880 --> 53:10.760
made decisions. For example, one African scientist said,

53:10.760 --> 53:17.720
"'Thank you, Mr. Price. Thank you for the papers. They are very interesting. I shall

53:17.720 --> 53:28.600
order 15 S3Bs and 400 M2Gs.'" So Max was very popular with the other directors.

53:28.600 --> 53:35.680
"'Excellent work, Max,' said the finance director one day. "'Yes, excellent,' said the

53:35.680 --> 53:47.600
company's vice-chairman. "'We have a surprise for you, Max. You are now the new chairman of FSI.'"

53:47.600 --> 53:53.280
Me? The chairman of FSI?

53:53.280 --> 54:22.400
Chapter 7. The Sky is the Limit. Now Max was the chairman of Friendship Services International.

54:22.400 --> 54:31.520
Now he was at the top of the star building. His office was on the 25th floor. It was a very

54:31.520 --> 54:40.040
strange office. It was a very large white room. There was a big desk and one chair. On the desk

54:40.040 --> 54:46.440
there were two telephones. One telephone had the letter M on it. The other telephone had the

54:46.440 --> 54:56.360
letter W. Max said to himself, "'What are these phones for?' But he did not know. There was a

54:56.360 --> 55:03.920
very large window in the office. From the window Max looked out at the clear blue sky. He remembered

55:03.920 --> 55:11.360
the Friendship Services International advertisement. The sky is the limit. He remembered the interview

55:11.360 --> 55:17.360
with Mr. Lele, Mr. Creep, and Mort Hightower. Then he thought about Frank Stedman.

55:17.360 --> 55:26.960
"'Where's Frank now?' Max thought. But Max did not know. And Max remembered his wife Angela and his

55:26.960 --> 55:35.720
children Stephen and Juliet. They never came back. Every evening Max went home to an empty house. But

55:35.720 --> 55:44.600
now his beautiful home was dirty. Nobody visited Max. He had no friends. He was alone. He was unhappy.

55:45.960 --> 55:50.440
Every evening Max wrote a letter. Every letter was the same.

55:52.040 --> 56:01.160
"'My darling Angela, please come home. I need you. I love you. Please bring the children. I love

56:01.160 --> 56:11.880
them too. Where are you Angela? Please come home. All my love, Max. Max put each letter into an envelope.

56:12.600 --> 56:19.320
On every envelope Max wrote, "'To my darling Angela. Now there were nearly a hundred letters.

56:20.280 --> 56:29.880
They were all the same.'" Max was chairman of FSI, but he had no work. Every day he came to his office.

56:30.520 --> 56:37.240
But every day there was no work. One morning he found a large book on his desk.

56:38.520 --> 56:40.600
"'What's this?" he asked himself.

56:42.760 --> 56:47.000
At that moment the M telephone rang. Max picked it up.

56:47.800 --> 56:54.680
A voice said, "'Send us five hundred N-five B's immediately. He will find details in the catalog."

56:55.640 --> 57:03.640
"'But who are you?" asked Max. "'And what are N-five B's?'" Max waited, but there was no answer.

57:04.920 --> 57:09.960
The W telephone rang. Max picked it up. Another voice said,

57:10.600 --> 57:15.640
"'Send us five hundred N-five B's immediately. You will find details in the catalog.'"

57:17.000 --> 57:22.440
"'But who are you?" Max asked again. "'And what are N-five B's?'"

57:23.400 --> 57:29.240
Again Max waited, but there was no answer. He was now frightened.

57:30.680 --> 57:39.160
"'Who is M?' said Max. "'And who is W? And N-five B? What is N-five B?'"

57:40.360 --> 57:44.520
Max picked up the catalog on his desk. He opened it at N.

57:44.520 --> 58:01.560
"'N-five B. N-nuclear. Five, missile. B, star blast. General information. One, for land,

58:01.560 --> 58:05.480
sea, or air. Two, instant kill.'"

58:06.360 --> 58:13.640
"'Oh, no. I'm selling missiles. Guns. Bombs.'"

58:18.840 --> 58:23.800
"'I didn't know. I didn't know. What shall I do?'"

58:24.120 --> 58:30.040
"'The sky. The sky.'"

58:45.560 --> 58:51.560
The Skies the Limit was read by Peter Whitman and the recording produced by James Richardson at

58:51.560 --> 58:54.120
Studio AVP London.

